    • Constructor Detail

      • OrCondition

        @SafeVarargs
public OrCondition(Condition<T>... conditions)
        Initializes the or operator with none, one or several sub-conditions. 
         Condition<String> condition1 = ...
 Condition<String> condition2 = ...
 OrCondition<String> myCondition = new OrCondition<>(condition1, condition2);
        Has the same effect as: 
         Condition<String> condition1 = ...
 Condition<String> condition2 = ...
 OrCondition<String> myCondition = new OrCondition<>();
 myCondition.or(condition1);
 myCondition.or(condition2);
        Parameters:
        conditions - the conditions to register (order is important)

      • or

        public OrCondition<T> or(Condition<T> condition)
        Adds a condition to the current condition. For example: 
         OrCondition<String> myCondition = new OrCondition<>();
 myCondition.or(new FixedCondition<>(true));
 myCondition.apply("foo"); // will always return true
 
 myCondition.or(new FixedCondition<>(false));
 myCondition.apply("foo"); // will always return false
        The returned instance is the same as myCondition so you can also write this: 
         OrCondition<String> myCondition = new OrCondition<>();
 myCondition = myCondition.or(new FixedCondition<>(true));
 myCondition.apply("foo"); // will always return true
 
 myCondition = myCondition.or(new FixedCondition<>(false));
 myCondition.apply("foo"); // will always return true because first
                                                        // condition always returns true
        Parameters:
        condition - the condition to add
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining

      • or

        public OrCondition<T> or(List<Condition<T>> conditions)
        Adds several conditions at once to the current condition. This can be useful when you register each sub-condition into a list: 
         List<Condition<String>> conditions = new ArrayList<>();
 conditions.add(...);
 conditions.add(...);
 OrCondition<String> myCondition = new OrCondition<>();
 myCondition.or(conditions);
        Parameters:
        conditions - the list of conditions to register
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining
